  _id: master-voss
  _characterName: Master Voss
  _role: Tax collector / Aldric's messenger
  _age: Late forties
  _home: On the road and Lord Aldric's estate
  _work: Tax collection, ledgers, and official deliveries
  _keepsake: Tax ledger
  _tagline: A tired professional carrying exact figures through an inexact hardship.
  _leadParagraph: Master Voss is gaunt, plain, and controlled, with a drab coat and
    a ledger satchel held close.
  _backgroundParagraph: He arrives in Hollowfen as Lord Aldric's collector, counts
    what the village owes without raising his voice, and later returns carrying a
    sealed letter.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Voss separates sympathy from duty because his work requires
    it. His smallest changes in posture say more than a speech would.
  _kitItems: []
  _heroPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  _pullquote: I am not unsympathetic, but I am also not paid to be sympathetic.
